  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Events in Vue?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Events in Vue are used to handle user interactions such as clicks, typing, and form submissions."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Event Handling"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<button @click=\"handleClick\">Click</button>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Inline Event"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<button @click=\"count++\">Increment</button>\n<p>{{ count }}</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Methods Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "methods: {\n  handleClick() {\n    alert('Clicked');\n  }\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Passing Arguments"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<button @click=\"greet('Vue')\">Greet</button>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Event Object"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<button @click=\"handleClick($event)\">Click</button>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Emitting Events (Child to Parent)"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "this.$emit('customEvent', data);"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Listening to Emitted Events"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<child-component @customEvent=\"handleEvent\"></child-component>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Event Modifiers"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**.stop → Stop propagation**",
        "**.prevent → Prevent default action**",
        "**.once → Trigger once**",
        "**.self → Only trigger on element itself**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Keyboard Events"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<input @keyup.enter=\"submit\">"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Use methods for complex logic**",
        "**Use emit for component communication**",
        "**Keep event handlers simple**",
        "**Use modifiers effectively**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Common Mistakes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Writing complex logic inline**",
        "**Not using emit for communication**",
        "**Ignoring event modifiers**",
        "**Incorrect event naming**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conclusion"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Vue events provide a powerful way to handle user interactions and component communication efficiently."
    }
  ],

  "faq": [
    {
      "question": "What is @click?",
      "answer": "It listens to click events."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is $emit?",
      "answer": "It sends events from child to parent."
    },
    {
      "question": "What are event modifiers?",
      "answer": "They modify event behavior like prevent or stop."
    }
  ],

